          Conclusion
        </h2>
        <p class="mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          Understanding addiction as a brain disease rather than a moral failing is crucial for 
          developing effective prevention and treatment strategies. The neuroscience of addiction 
          helps explain why willpower alone is often insufficient for overcoming substance use 
          disorders and why professional treatment is typically necessary.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">
          By recognizing the complex interplay of genetic, environmental, and developmental factors 
          that contribute to addiction, we can approach this disorder with compassion, reduce stigma, 
          and provide evidence-based treatments that address the underlying brain changes associated 
          with addiction. This scientific understanding provides hope for those struggling with addiction 
          and their loved ones, highlighting that recovery is possible with proper support and treatment.
        </p>
